    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "\"profoundly unique\" is exactly what it feels like. it's actually scary. i was looking at a silver ring in a shop window today and i got this sudden, sickening wave of grief, like i was mourning someone. then i saw a headline about a passing in a different city. it's like the objects are tethered to the events they're part of. if science doesn't recognize it, does that mean there's some kind of pattern i'm just not seeing the math for? like, is there a way to actually map these echoes so it's not just random chaos?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
